                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="3047.831" end="x">Now you stayed for about a month with the German Red Cross. What happened afterwards?</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Anna Braun</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#braunA" start="3057.624" end="x">Then the German soldiers were demobilized or sent away somewhere that I don't know. And the deportees and refugees remained alone in the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>. And so these refugees and deportees elected a man and there comes a new mayor to the town and he ordered that this man should now be in charge of the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>, he should handle the administration, and that a new chef should be chosen for the kitchen or be appointed. And so I too was assigned to the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a> kitchen as second cook. And so I did the cooking for nine months.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
